@NODE Tut_Load_Save
@TITLE "Chapter 4   Loading & Saving"

Loading & Saving
****************
	There are  different files that Scheduler saves out, each with
it's own extension. The name that Scheduler uses to save the files is 
the default name in the Icon @{" ToolTypes. " link ToolTypes} This also holds 
the directory where it will be placed.

e.g.. if the name was "DEFNAME=sample" and your directory was 
"DEFDRWER=System:Scheduler" then your Scheduler file would be saved at
"System:Scheduler/sample.sch".

The File Extensions Are:
------------------------
  ".sch"     e.g.. "default.sch"      Scheduler file
  ".phb"     e.g.. "default.phb"      PhoneBook file
  ".cal"     e.g.. "default.cal"      Calendar file
  ".prefs"   e.g.. "default.prefs"    Preferences file


Scheduler File  (".sch")
------------------------
	The first is the most useful way, to save a Scheduler file. ('.sch')
This has all of your PhoneBooks, and all of their entries. So now lets 
save out your scheduler file the quickest way. Select 'Save' from the 
Scheduler menu on the PhoneBook menu. You should see your Hard drive or 
Floppy drive light blink on as it saves out the file. This is the quickest
cause Scheduler already knows the name the file should be and where it
 belongs. The second way is to select 'Save As' from the Scheduler menu. 
This brings up a requester asking you what you what the file called, and 
where you want to put it. This allows you to save your file, as a different 
name or in a different place than the default.
	
	To Load the file back in just select 'Open' from the Scheduler menu
and select the file you wish to Load. This will clear out your current
data and load in the new.


PhoneBook File  (".phb")
------------------------
	The second way is to just save out your current phonebook. Select
'Save PhoneBook...' from the PhoneBook menu in the PhoneBook window.
This brings up the requester asking you what and where you want the file.
	
	To load the PhoneBook back in, select 'Open PhoneBook...'. Now you
are presented with a requester that asks if you wish to 'Overwrite' or
to 'Append'. Overwrite will erase your current PhoneBook, and load in
the new one in it's place. Append will simply Add this PhoneBook to
your files.
	
	The last option is to append one phonebook to an another. Select
'Append PhoneBook...' and select the file you wish to append. Now your
PhoneBook contains the contents of your old data, and the new.


Calendar File  (".cal")
-----------------------
	The Save and the Save As work the same way as the Scheduler Save and
Save As. Currently there is no Append for the Calendar.

Preferences File (".prefs")
---------------------------
	The Save and the Save As work the same way as the Scheduler Save and
Save As, with one exception, the Save is a button and not a menu item.

@ENDNODE

@NODE ToolTypes
@TITLE "Chapter 5   ToolTypes"

ToolTypes
*********

	ToolTypes that are found in the Scheduler icon.

  DEFNAME=                 The default name used when loading and saving.
  DEFDRAWER=               The default path used when loading and saving.
  HOTKEY=                  The key sequence to open Scheduler's window 
                                              when hidden
  POPUP=(yes,no)           Open the window when first run
  DONOTWAIT                If run from the WBStartup Drawer you must have
                                              this
@ENDNODE

